INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter and the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to improving access to city services for limited English proficiency individuals
EventItemMatterName: Improving access to city services for limited English proficiency individuals.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Developmental Disability, Alcoholism, Substance Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Office of Alcoholism and Substance Abuse Services to require that all addiction treatment facilities and programs use evidence-based treatment and make public comprehensive information about which treatment approaches are used and long-term patient outcomes.
EventItemMatterName: Require that all addiction treatment facilities and programs use evidence-based treatment and make public comprehensive information about which treatment approaches are used and long-term patient outcomes.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to modification and removal of certain deed restrictions
EventItemMatterName: Removing deed restrictions placed on city properties when they are sold or otherwise disposed of.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Developmental Disability, Alcoholism, Substance Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring arrestee health screenings and the exchange of health information of inmates in the custody of the department of correction
EventItemMatterName: Arrestee health screenings and the exchange of health information of inmates in the custody of the department of correction.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Parks and Recreation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to locking playgrounds in city parks.
EventItemMatterName: Locking playgrounds in city parks.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Aging
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing certain information to users of life-sustaining equipment and individuals for whom a disruption in electrical service would create a medical emergency
EventItemMatterName: Providing certain information to users of life-sustaining equipment and individuals for whom a disruption in electrical service would create a medical emergency.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Rights
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to amending the definitions of sexual orientation and gender in the New York city human rights law
EventItemMatterName: Amending the definitions of sexual orientation and gender in the New York city human rights law.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to a report on obtaining government-issued identification for youth
EventItemMatterName: Report on obtaining government-issued identification for youth.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to interest rate charged for the nonpayment of water and sewer charges.
EventItemMatterName: Interest rate charged for the nonpayment of water and sewer charges.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution to establish that the discount percentage for early payment of real estate taxes be set at one-half of one percent per annum for Fiscal Year 2017.
EventItemMatterName: Establish that the discount percentage for early payment of real estate taxes be set at one-half of one percent per annum for FY'17.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution to establish that the interest rate be 6 percent per annum for Fiscal Year 2017 for non-payment of taxes on properties with an assessed value of not more than $250,000, or not more than $250,000 per residential unit for cooperative apartments.
EventItemMatterName: Establish that the interest rate be 6 percent per annum for FY'17 for non-payment of taxes on properties with an assessed value of not more than $250,000, or not more than $250,000 per residential unit for cooperative apartments.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution to establish that the interest rate be 18 percent per annum for Fiscal Year 2017 for non-payment of taxes on properties with an assessed value of over $250,000, or over $250,000 per residential unit for cooperative apartments.
EventItemMatterName: Establish that the interest rate be 18 percent per annum for FY'17 for non-payment of taxes on properties with an assessed value of over $250,000, or over $250,000 per residential unit for cooperative apartments.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution to establish that the interest rate to be charged for Fiscal Year 2017 for non-payment of water rents and sewer rents be 9 percent per annum.
EventItemMatterName: Establish that the interest rate to be charged forFY'17 for non-payment of water rents and sewer rents be 9 percent per annum.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Developmental Disability, Alcoholism, Substance Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to a pilot program for the use of beacon navigation technology.
EventItemMatterName: A pilot program for the use of beacon navigation technology.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to a foster care task force
EventItemMatterName: Foster care task force.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to a report on the educational continuity of children in foster care
EventItemMatterName: Report on the educational continuity of children in foster care.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to a five-year plan to address barriers to permanency
EventItemMatterName: Certain children who have spent the greatest length of time in foster care.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, S.6303/A.1719, which would provide a beer production tax credit to registered distributors that produce beer within New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Provide a beer production tax credit to registered distributors that produce beer within NYC. (S.6303/A.1719-A)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of education to report information on computer science education in New York city schools
EventItemMatterName: Requiring DOE to report information on computer science education in NYC schools.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to clarifying the responsibilities of youth leagues with respect to defibrillators.
EventItemMatterName: Clarifying the responsibilities of youth leagues with respect to defibrillators.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the mayor’s office of operations to report on adult literacy programs offered by the city or pursuant to a contract with the city.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the mayor’s office of operations to report on adult literacy programs offered by the city or pursuant to a contract with the city.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to a report on permanency indicators
EventItemMatterName: Report on permanency indicators.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to proof of service of certain required mailings for applications to the board of standards and appeals
EventItemMatterName: Proof of service of certain required mailings for applications to the board of standards and appeals.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to foster care experience surveys
EventItemMatterName: Surveys for youth in foster care regarding experiences with foster parents.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to flood mitigation in southeast Queens
EventItemMatterName: Flood mitigation in southeast Queens.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey to widen the George Washington Bridge’s sidewalks.
EventItemMatterName: Port Authority of NY and NJ to widen the George Washington Bridge’s sidewalks.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign legislation that would increase the amount of housing subsidy from $300 to $600 per month, and extend the age eligibility from 21 to 24 for youth who have aged out of foster care
EventItemMatterName: Increase the amount of housing subsidy from $300 to $600 per month, and to extend the age eligibility from 21 to 24 for youth who have aged out of foster care.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to waiving parking violations when a parking sign is illegible.
EventItemMatterName: Waiving parking violations when a parking sign is illegible.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Metropolitan Transportation Authority to end MetroCard expiration dates.
EventItemMatterName: MTA to end MetroCard expiration dates.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation that would eliminate the cap on the number of speed cameras allowed to be deployed in school zones in New York City and remove the authorizing law’s sunset provision.
EventItemMatterName: Eliminate the cap on the number of speed cameras allowed to be deployed in school zones in NYC and remove the authorizing law’s sunset provision.
